so that when we click, it's already there.

56
00:03:43.262 --> 00:03:46.835
So this is another thing that
Gatsby is doing in the background,

57
00:03:46.835 --> 00:03:50.079
when you hover over a link
It'll start prefetching data so

58
00:03:50.079 --> 00:03:53.538
that you don't have to wait as
long after you click that link.

59
00:03:53.538 --> 00:03:56.263
And a lot of times,
I'm gonna go here and I'm gonna click,

60
00:03:56.263 --> 00:03:58.020
that's maybe 500 milliseconds.

61
00:03:58.020 --> 00:04:00.630
500 milliseconds can
make a big difference.

62
00:04:00.630 --> 00:04:05.950
If something happens in under a second or
so, it feels instant.

63
00:04:05.950 --> 00:04:08.150
It's a very nice experience.

64
00:04:08.150 --> 00:04:12.378
And if the difference in me
clicking is one second or one and

65
00:04:12.378 --> 00:04:15.397
a half seconds in terms
of how long I wait,

66
00:04:15.397 --> 00:04:21.460
that can make the difference between
my app feeling a little slow or native.

67
00:04:21.460 --> 00:04:26.851
And that's the little things that we all
want to do when we build custom apps, but

68
00:04:26.851 --> 00:04:32.350
